OL,3,CRob Burrow: What is motor neurone
OL,4,Cdisease?
OL,6,FThe MND Association says some people
OL,7,Falso experience changes to their
OL,8,Fthinking and behaviour.
OL,10,FWhat are the early signs of MND?
OL,12,FThe NHS says MND symptoms occur
OL,13,Fgradually so may not be obvious at
OL,14,Ffirst.
OL,16,FEarly symptoms include weakness in
OL,17,Fankles or legs, slurred speech,
OL,18,Fdifficulty swallowing food, a weak
OL,19,Fgrip, muscle cramps and twitches and
OL,20,Fweight loss.
