OL,3,CRob Burrow: What is motor neurone
OL,4,Cdisease?
OL,6,FWhat causes MND?
OL,8,FThe health service says it is caused
OL,9,Fby a problem with cells in the brain
OL,10,Fand motor neurones.
OL,12,FIt is not known why these cells and
OL,13,Fneurones gradually stop working over
OL,14,Ftime.
OL,16,FThe NHS says having a close relative
OL,17,Fwith MND, or a related condition
OL,18,Fcalled frontotemporal dementia, can
OL,19,Fsometimes mean you are more likely to
OL,20,Fget it, but in most cases it does not
OL,21,Frun in families.
